This paper discusses the pricing of Internet resources, which is closely related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses economic models and optimization methods, which are related to game theory and algorithm design, respectively. Therefore, cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper discusses resource allocation and optimization, which are related to distributed computing and data centers. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a likely category. Finally, the paper discusses security and privacy issues related to resource pricing, which are related to cryptography and computer security. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a possible category.
